<div id="review_1652860468" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1652860468" />
    <a title="Wittch" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1253816-wittch"><img alt="Wittch" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1431743610p2/1253816.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1652860468?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Wittch" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Wittch" href="/user/show/1253816-wittch">Wittch</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1652860468" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4632822617509285502">This book was absolutely fascinating. Mendelsohn counterpoints the Holocaust with discussions of Old Testament interpretations. Especially his discussion of the story of Cain and Abel shed a whole new light on sibling rivalry. People who are interested in their own family histories would find a whole new perspective on their research. This is the best book I have read in 2016.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


